title: Richard Groove Holmes - Super Soul PR 7497 VBR
description:
Richard "Groove" Holmes
Super Soul
-----------------------

This is the grooviest Hammond B3 player, Richard "Groove" Holmes, in action, accompanied by a big band.  Released in 1967, this album features Holmes' tendency to have a bit of fun with the draw-bars of the Hammond B3.  He enjoyed creating "unusual" tonal qualities which became part of his own, distinct style and sound.

Enjoy the tunes.  Please keep seeding as long as you can.


 1   Why Don't You Do Right?
 2   Ain't That Peculiar
 3   In Between the Heartaches
 4   Function at the Junction
 5   On Green Dolphin Street
 6   I Will Wait for You
 7   (Back Home Again In) Indiana
 8   Tennessee Waltz
 9   Bluesette 
10   Super Soul
